{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 1,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "The Pharisees also with the Sadducees came, and tempting desired him that he would shew them a sign from heaven."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 2,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "He answered"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "and said unto them",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 3,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 4,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And he left them, and departed."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 5,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And when his disciples were come to the other side, they had forgotten to take bread."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "said unto them",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Warning about Leaven"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And they reasoned among themselves, saying,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "It is because we have taken no bread.",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 8,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Which when Jesus perceived,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "he said unto them",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 9,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 10,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 11,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 12,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then understood they how that he bade them not beware of the leaven of bread, but of the doctrine of the Pharisees and of the Sadducees."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 13,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "When Jesus came into the coasts of Caesarea Philippi,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "he asked his disciples, saying",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Peter's Confession of Christ"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 14,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Some say that thou art John the Baptist: some, Elias; and others, Jeremias, or one of the prophets.",
          "speaker": "Disciples"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 15,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "saith unto them",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 16,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Thou art the Christ, the Son of the living God.",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 17,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "answered and said unto him",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 18,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then charged he his disciples that they should tell no man that he was Jesus the Christ."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "From that time forth began Jesus to shew unto his disciples, how that he must go unto Jerusalem, and suffer many things of the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be killed, and be raised again the third day."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Jesus Predicts His Death"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then Peter took him, and began to rebuke him, saying,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "Be it far from thee, Lord: this shall not be unto thee.",
          "speaker": "Peter"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "But he turned,"
        },
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "and said unto Peter",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "divine",
          "text": "said unto his disciples",
          "speaker": "Jesus"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "The Way of the Cross"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 26,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 27,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 28,
      "segments": [],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}